{
  "texts": [
    "Cross-disciplinary collaboration is becoming increasingly vital for advancing olfactory and gustatory research.",
    "The integration of neuroscience, computer science, and food science can significantly deepen our understanding of sensory mechanisms and foster innovative applications.",
    "For instance, combining neuroimaging technologies (Su et al. 2024) with advanced machine learning algorithms enables researchers to analyze consumers' neural responses 1 3 to various food flavors in real time.",
    "This multifaceted approach offers insights into how different ingredients affect not only sensory perception but also emotional responses, guiding researchers to optimize product formulations effectively.",
    "Understanding the neural correlates of flavor preferences can help pinpoint which specific spices or flavor components most influence consumers' purchasing decisions."
  ]
}